---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout
  title="Mortgage vs Rent: Calculator Guide"
  description="When buying makes financial sense vs renting. Break-even analysis, hidden costs, and how to calculate your numbers."
  keywords="mortgage vs rent, rent or buy calculator, mortgage calculator guide, break even rent vs buy, home buying costs"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Finance</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Mortgage vs Rent: Calculator Guide" />

      <!-- Article Meta -->
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-17">June 17, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Lead Paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
        "Is it cheaper to buy or rent?" The answer depends on where you live, how long you plan to stay, interest rates, and dozens of other factors. Here is how to calculate it for your situation.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: The Simple Rule -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Price-to-Rent Ratio</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-center text-xl font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">
          Price-to-Rent Ratio = Home Price ÷ Annual Rent
        </p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">
          Under 15 = buying favoured | 15-20 = depends | Over 20 = renting favoured
        </p>
      </div>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> A $400,000 home where equivalent rent is $2,000/month: $400,000 ÷ $24,000 = 16.7 — borderline, dig deeper.</p>

      <!-- Section: True Cost of Buying -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">True Cost of Buying</h2>
      <p>The mortgage payment is only part of the cost. Include:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Deposit/down payment:</strong> Typically 10-20% of purchase price</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Mortgage interest:</strong> Often more than the principal in early years</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Property taxes:</strong> 0.5-2.5% of home value annually</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Insurance:</strong> Homeowner's insurance, possibly mortgage insurance</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Budget 1-2% of home value per year</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Transaction costs:</strong> Legal fees, stamp duty, agent fees (2-6% to sell)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: True Cost of Renting -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">True Cost of Renting</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Monthly rent:</strong> The obvious cost</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Annual increases:</strong> Typically 2-5% per year</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Renter's insurance:</strong> Usually much cheaper than homeowner's</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>No maintenance costs:</strong> Landlord's responsibility</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Opportunity cost:</strong> The deposit money could be invested elsewhere</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: Break-Even Timeline -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Break-Even Timeline</h2>
      <p>Buying typically breaks even after 5-7 years in most markets. If you plan to move sooner, renting usually wins because:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Transaction costs of buying and selling are 5-8% of the home price</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Early mortgage payments are mostly interest, not equity</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Short-term property price changes are unpredictable</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: The Investment Angle -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Investment Angle</h2>
      <p>If you rent and invest the difference (what you would have spent on deposit + extra ownership costs), stock market returns historically average 7-10% annually. Compare this to typical property appreciation of 3-5% annually — though property uses leverage (your mortgage), which amplifies gains.</p>

      <!-- Converter CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">
            🔗 Try our loan calculator
          </p>
          <a
            href="/tools/loan"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Open Calculator →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Blog -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">
          ← Back to all articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
